LAYER 3: CONNECTIVITY AND PATHFINDING
how Fadriel sees connections that span distance

observe spatial_perception.rana
observe spatial_superposition.rana

this is the COUPLING property made spatial:
two cells are connected if there is a PATH of non-zero cells between them
connection is not just adjacency — it is REACHABILITY

@spatial_rule flood_fill_transform
DETECT connected components via flood fill
APPLY different transforms to different components
LEARN component → transform mapping
VERIFY component-specific transform matches output
APPLY component transform for test
SPEECH "each connected region gets its own treatment"

@spatial_rule connect_dots
DETECT isolated dots of same color
DRAW lines between dots (horizontal, vertical, or shortest path)
FILL the path between each pair with a specific color
VERIFY connections match output for all pairs
APPLY connect dots in test
SPEECH "I draw lines between the dots"

@spatial_rule path_trace
DETECT a start point and end point (marked by specific colors)
TRACE a path from start to end (following walls, avoiding obstacles)
MARK the path in the output
VERIFY path matches output
APPLY trace path in test
SPEECH "I follow the path from {start} to {end}"

@spatial_rule propagate_color
DETECT seed cells (specific color)
PROPAGATE color outward from seeds following rules
(only through zero cells? only horizontally? until hitting obstacle?)
LEARN propagation rules from training
VERIFY propagation matches output
APPLY propagate from seeds in test
SPEECH "color spreads from each seed"

@spatial_rule connected_recolor
DETECT connected components
RECOLOR each component based on its properties (size, shape, position)
LEARN property → color mapping
VERIFY recoloring matches output
APPLY connected recolor for test
SPEECH "each connected region gets recolored by its {property}"

the key to connectivity:
LOCAL adjacency is not enough
TWO cells can be connected through a CHAIN of neighbors
this chain can be any length
connection is TRANSITIVE: if A connects to B and B connects to C then A connects to C

connectivity properties:
- connected component count
- component sizes
- bridges (cells whose removal disconnects components)
- articulation points
- shortest path between two cells
- whether two cells are in the same component

this is COUPLING at scale:
two qu-septits are coupled if measuring one tells you about the other
two cells are connected if changing one would affect the other
connection through the grid IS entanglement through space

@perceive connectivity
DETECT connected components via flood fill
MEASURE component count, sizes, shapes
DETECT bridges and articulation points
LEARN which connectivity properties determine the output
